content.description: Sit start with the beautiful undercling. Dance your way up to the arête using knee bars, toe hooks, and any other trick you got. At some point the arête becomes less cooprative forcing you to dig even deeper into your steezey bank. Hand traverse the high horizontal crack to a rediculously cool mantle.
content.protection: 3-4 pads, a good spotter, or a brave climber.
content.location: Located on the first big boulder. On the lookers right as you approach.

content.description:
40 feet uphill of The Moudra topout is a fin-shaped boulder. Dry Fire climbs the left side of that boulder when seen from downhill.

Start matched on a flat rail about 4 feet left of a small dihedral feature. Traverse right and then up past a roof. Fun movement on pretty good holds, with some long, satisfying pulls.

Named because I dry fired spectacularly on my second to last go, enabling Haychoi to get the first ascent. I climbed it right after, bleeding all over the place.
content.protection: There's some fairly big fall potential at the crux, but the sequence we used ended up feeling pretty safe.

climbs.name: Ain’t Nothin’ but a Hueco Thing

content.description: Start on low right facing side pulls and crimp up and left to a top out in the corner.
content.location: On The Moudra boulder. This climb is on the side of the boulder that faces the road. Small overhang next to a corner.
